  "text": "## HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 Header Normalization Migration - Analysis\n\nThe Envoy proxy implements HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 header translation through several coordinated components:\n\n### 1. HTTP/1.1 Header Parsing and Normalization\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc`\n\nThe HTTP/1.1 codec parser normalizes all header names to lowercase during parsing:\n- **Line 565**: `current_header_field_.inlineTransform([](char c) { return absl::ascii_tolower(c); });` performs case normalization of header field names\n- **Lines 1218**: Sets the request method via `headers->setMethod(parser_->methodName())`\n- **Lines 1141-1145**: Sets the scheme with lowercase normalization: `headers.setScheme(absl::AsciiStrToLower(absolute_url.scheme()))`\n- **Line 1159**: Sets the path via `headers.setPath(absolute_url.pathAndQueryParams())`\n- **Line 1141**: Sets host/authority via `headers.setHost(absolute_url.hostAndPort())`\n\n### 2. HTTP/1.1 Parser Implementations\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/http1/`\n- `codec_impl.cc/h`: Main codec implementation that handles parsing and encoding\n- `balsa_parser.cc/h`: HTTP/1.1 message parser based on Balsa library\n- `legacy_parser_impl.cc/h`: Alternative parser implementation\n- `header_formatter.cc/h`: Handles header name formatting (ProperCase, etc.)\n\n### 3. Pseudo-Header Injection and Mapping\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/header_map_impl.cc`\n\nThe header map implementation contains a special case at line 124 that maps HTTP/1.1's legacy \"Host\" header to HTTP/2's \":authority\" pseudo-header:\n```cpp\n// Special case where we map a legacy host header to :authority.\nconst auto handle = CustomInlineHeaderRegistry::getInlineHeader<RequestHeaderMap::header_map_type>(\n    Headers::get().Host);\ninput.emplace_back(\n    Headers::get().HostLegacy.get(), [handle](HeaderMapImpl& h) -> StaticLookupResponse {\n      return {&h.inlineHeaders()[handle.value().it_->second], &handle.value().it_->first};\n    });\n```\n\n**Pseudo-Header Definitions**: `source/common/http/headers.h` defines:\n- `:method` (line 221)\n- `:path` (line 222)\n- `:scheme` (line 228)\n- `:authority` (line 216, mapped from Host)\n\n### 4. HTTP/2 Codec Encoding\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.cc`\n\nThe HTTP/2 codec receives already-normalized headers and encodes them:\n- **Lines 274-307**: `ConnectionImpl::ClientStreamImpl::encodeHeaders()` processes request headers\n- **Lines 310-330**: `ConnectionImpl::ServerStreamImpl::encodeHeaders()` processes response headers\n- **Lines 250-257**: `ConnectionImpl::StreamImpl::buildHeaders()` constructs the HTTP/2 header vector from the header map\n\n### 5. Upgrade Header Handling and Transformation\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/utility.cc`\n\nUpgrade header transformations between HTTP/1 and HTTP/2:\n- **Line 1047**: `Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH1toH2()` - Converts HTTP/1 Upgrade requests to HTTP/2 CONNECT requests\n  - Sets method to CONNECT\n  - Sets :protocol pseudo-header\n  - Removes Upgrade and Connection headers\n- **Line 1065**: `Utility::transformUpgradeResponseFromH1toH2()` - Converts HTTP/1 101 responses to HTTP/2 200 responses\n- **Line 1080**: `Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH2toH1()` - Reverse transformation\n- **Line 1093**: `Utility::transformUpgradeResponseFromH2toH1()` - Reverse transformation\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc`\n\nUpgrade header removal/sanitization:\n- Conditionally removes Upgrade header for non-upgrade requests\n- Sanitizes Connection header per RFC 7230\n\n### 6. Header Validation and Utilities\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/header_utility.cc`\n\n- **Line 679**: `HeaderUtility::isPseudoHeader()` - Identifies pseudo-headers (names starting with ':')\n- **Line 238**: `HeaderUtility::authorityIsValid()` - Validates :authority pseudo-header format\n- **Line 444**: `HeaderUtility::requestHeadersValid()` - Validates request headers including pseudo-headers\n- **Line 489**: `HeaderUtility::checkRequiredRequestHeaders()` - Ensures required pseudo-headers (:method, :path, :authority, :scheme) are present\n\n### 7. HTTP/1 to gRPC/HTTP/2 Bridges\n\n**Location**: `source/extensions/filters/http/grpc_http1_bridge/http1_bridge_filter.cc`\n\nSpecialized bridge for gRPC requests over HTTP/1:\n- Detects gRPC requests and handles protocol conversion\n- Manages gRPC frame header processing\n\n**Location**: `source/extensions/filters/http/grpc_http1_reverse_bridge/filter.cc`\n\nReverse bridge for converting HTTP/2 gRPC responses back to HTTP/1:\n- Transforms content-type headers\n- Manages gRPC status codes and message translation\n\n### 8. Connection Manager Integration\n\n**Location**: `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc` and `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h`\n\nIntegrates the codecs and manages upgrade requests:\n- Line 1194: Sanitizes Connection header for non-upgrade requests\n- Tracks successful upgrades and manages stream state\n\n## Summary\n\nThe HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 header translation in Envoy is a multi-stage process:\n1. **Parsing**: HTTP/1.1 codec normalizes header names to lowercase and extracts request line components\n2. **Pseudo-header Injection**: HTTP/1.1 components are converted to HTTP/2 pseudo-headers through the header map API (Host → :authority)\n3. **Validation**: Header utilities validate pseudo-header presence and format\n4. **Encoding**: HTTP/2 codec serializes the normalized headers with pseudo-headers in the proper format\n5. **Upgrade Handling**: Special transformation logic converts HTTP/1 Upgrade requests to HTTP/2 CONNECT requests\n"
}

